Package owlSpeak.engine

This package provides all classes the controller needs to generate the next dialogue steps.

See: Description

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AgendaPrio
    The class that encapsulates the calculation of the Agenda priority
    Core
    contains the ontologies-Vector, the OwlSpeakOntology actualOnto and the RespawnManager respawnManager
    CoreMove
    owlSpeak Class CoreMove is the basic Move/Agenda/OwlSpeakOntology triplet used for the engine
    MasterSlot
    The class that represents all POMDP Slots.
    OwlScript
    The class that is used for evaluating the OwlScript expressions
    OwlSpeakOntology
    encapsulates all OwlSpeakOntology access
    ProbModel
    The class that maintains all the probabilities required for updating the belief states of a Slot.
    RespawnManager
    owlSpeak Class RespawnManager allows access to multiple Respawn and encapsulates reading / writing
    ServletEngine
    The object that contains the Core object and the VoiceDocument functions
    Settings
    owlSpeak Class Settings is used for reading / writing the settings of the Controller
    Slot
    The class that represents a POMDP Slot.
